1-million-to-india-donald-trump-on-doge-cuts-7742802%23pfrom%3Dhome-ndtv_topscroll_Imagetopscroll%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EUS%20President%20Donald%20Trump%3C%2Fa%3E%20made%20it%20clear%20that%20India%20will%20not%20be%20spared%20from%20Washington's%20reciprocal%20tariffs.%20In%20a%20conversation%20with%20Fox%20News'%20Sean%20Hannity%2C%20President%20Trump%20reiterated%20his%20stance%20on%20global%20trade%20and%20existing%20tariff%20structures%20between%20the%20US%20and%20its%20partners.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20told%20Prime%20Minister%20(Narendra)%20Modi%20yesterday%20-%20he%20was%20here%20-%20I%20said%2C%20'Here's%20what%20we're%20going%20to%20do%3A%20reciprocal.%20Whatever%20you%20charge%2C%20I'm%20charging%2C'%26quot%3B%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22nofollow%2Cnoindex%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.whitehouse.gov%2Fremarks%2F2025%2F02%2Finterview-of-president-trump-and-elon-musk-by-sean-hannity-the-sean-hannity-show%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EPresident%20Trump%20said%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20recounting%20his%20conversation%20with%20the%20PM.%20%26quot%3BHe%20(PM%20Modi)%20goes%2C%20'No%2C%20no%2C%20I%20don't%20like%20that.'%20'No%2C%20no%2C%20whatever%20you%20charge%2C%20I'm%20going%20to%20charge.'%20I'm%20doing%20that%20with%20every%20country.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia%20has%20some%20of%20the%20world's%20highest%20tariffs%20on%20certain%20imports%20from%20the%20US%2C%20particularly%20in%20the%20automobile%20sector%2C%20where%20duties%20on%20foreign%20cars%20can%20reach%20up%20to%20100%20per%20cent.%20Mr%20Musk%2C%20sitting%20beside%20President%20Trump%2C%20confirmed%20this%2C%20saying%2C%20%26quot%3B%20It's%20100%20per%20cent%20-%20auto%20imports%20are%20100%20per%20cent.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPresident%20Trump%20responded%3A%20%26quot%3BYeah%2C%20that's%20peanuts.%20So%20much%20higher.%20And%20others%20too.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20argued%20that%20such%20tariffs%20make%20it%20nearly%20impossible%20for%20American%20companies%20to%20sell%20in%20India%20unless%20they%20establish%20manufacturing%20plants%20there%2C%20which%20he%20considers%20%26quot%3Bunfair%26quot%3B%20to%20the%20US%20economy.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUnder%20his%20proposed%20reciprocal%20tariff%20system%2C%20the%20US%20would%20impose%20the%20same%20level%20of%20tariffs%20on%20Indian%20imports%20as%20India%20levies%20on%20American%20goods.%20%26quot%3BNobody%20can%20argue%20with%20me%2C%26quot%3B%20President%20Trump%20insisted.%20%26quot%3BIf%20I%20said%2025%20per%20cent%2C%20they'd%20say%2C%20'Oh%2C%20that's%20terrible.'%20I%20don't%20say%20that%20anymore...%20because%20I%20say%2C%20'Whatever%20they%20charge%2C%20we'll%20charge.'%20And%20you%20know%20what%3F%20They%20stop.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20not%20the%20first%20time%20President%20Trump%20has%20clashed%20with%20India%20over%20tariffs.%20During%20his%20first%20term%2C%20he%20often%20referred%20to%20India%20as%20the%20%26quot%3Btariff%20king%26quot%3B%2C%20citing%20high%20import%20duties%20on%20US%20goods.%20Following%20Prime%20Minister%20Modi's%20recent%20visit%20to%20Washington%2C%20both%20countries%20committed%20to%20doubling%20bilateral%20trade%20to%20%24500%20billion%20by%202030%20and%20negotiating%20a%20bilateral%20trade%20agreement%20(BTA)%20by%20Autumn%202025.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1739948100000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-11%2Frk0ie17s_narendra-modi-donald-trump-modi-trump-afp_625x300_13_November_24.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fdonald-trump-heres-what-were-going-to-do-what-trump-told-pm-modi-on-reciprocal-tariffs-7744243%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22In%20a%20joint%20televised%20interview%20with%20billionaire%20Elon%20Musk%2C%20US%20President%20Donald%20Trump%20made%20it%20clear%20that%20India%20will%20not%20be%20spared%20from%20Washington's%20reciprocal%20tariffs.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fdonald-trump-heres-what-were-going-to-do-what-trump-told-pm-modi-on-reciprocal-tariffs-7744243%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Opinion%3A%20US%2C%20Russia%2C%20China%20Have%20Found%20A%20New%20'Negotiating%20Table'%20In%20Middle%20East%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EAs%20world%20leaders%20gathered%20in%20Munich%2C%20Germany%2C%20for%20Europe's%20top%20annual%20security%20conference%2C%20placating%2C%20pleasing%2C%20and%20managing%20US%20President%20Donald%20Trump%20stood%20as%20a%20top%20agenda.%20Trump's%20phone%20call%20to%20Russia's%20Vladimir%20Putin%2C%20US%20Vice-President%20J.D.%20Vance's%20disruptive%20speech%20challenging%20Europe%2C%20and%2C%20by%20association%2C%20the%20very%20nature%20of%20trans-Atlantic%20alliances%2C%20and%20demands%20to%20end%20the%20Ukraine%20conflict%2C%20has%20led%20to%20a%20mad%20rush%20to%20host%20such%20a%20process%2C%20in%20the%20Gulf.%20The%20question%20that%20perhaps%20comes%20immediately%20to%20mind%2C%20even%20though%20the%20conflict%20in%20Gaza%20remains%20a%20major%20global%20flashpoint%2C%20is%2C%20why%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Meeting%20Between%20Rubio%20And%20Lavrov%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERussia%20and%20the%20US%20are%20preparing%20to%20start%20initial%20consultations%20on%20Ukraine%20following%20an%20ice-breaking%20meeting%20between%20US%20Secretary%20of%20State%20Marco%20Rubio%20and%20Russia's%20Foreign%20Minister%20Sergei%20Lavrov%20in%20Saudi%20Arabia's%20capital%20Riyadh.%20For%20Saudi%20Arabia%20and%20its%20powerful%20heir-apparent%2C%20Crown%20Prince%20Mohammed%20bin%20Salman%2C%20this%20is%20a%20moment%20of%20both%20regional%20and%20global%20reckoning.%20Gulf%20powers%20in%20the%20Middle%20East%20have%20now%20been%20for%20a%20while%20re-positioning%20and%20re-posturing%20their%20geopolitics.%20This%20process%20started%20much%20before%20Trump's%20return%20to%20the%20White%20House%E2%80%94arguably%2C%20prior%20to%20even%20the%20Russian%20war%20against%20Ukraine.%20The%20roots%20of%20this%20shift%20lie%20in%20two%20main%20realities.%20First%2C%20a%20change%20in%20the%20construct%20of%20global%20power%20contestation%2C%20that%20is%2C%20a%20bi-polar%20competition%20between%20the%20US%20and%20China%20and%20a%20demand%20for%20multipolarity%20by%20a%20host%20of%20middle%20powers%20looking%20to%20secure%20their%20own%20interests%20and%20not%20get%20caught%20in%20the%20Washington-Beijing%20dynamics.%20The%20second%20reality%20relates%20to%20a%20general%20idea%20of%20the%20US%20becoming%20increasingly%20unwilling%20to%20mobilise%20militarily%20power%20to%20protect%20its%20allies.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EReconsidering%20America's%20Role%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERegional%20powers%20such%20as%20Saudi%20Arabia%20and%20the%20United%20Arab%20Emirates%20(UAE)%20are%20evaluating%20the%20very%20fundamentals%20of%20the%20decades-long%20American%20hegemony%2C%20which%20has%20provided%20security%20blankets%20in%20the%20region.%20This%20also%20provides%20them%20with%20an%20opportunity%20to%20build%20their%20own%20geopolitical%20repertoire%20as%20middle%20powers%20with%20their%20own%20agency%2C%20instead%20of%20being%20viewed%20as%20client%20states%2C%20a%20tag%20that%20has%20plagued%20many%20of%20them%20for%20decades.%20The%20UAE%20as%20well%20has%20thrown%20its%20hat%20into%20the%20ring%2C%20as%20Ukrainian%20President%20Volodymyr%20Zelenskyy%20landed%20in%20Abu%20Dhabi%2C%20mere%20hours%20after%20both%20Russia%20and%20the%20US%20eluded%20to%20excluding%20Kyiv%20from%20talks%20regarding%20Ukraine's%20own%20future%20(Zelenskyy%20later%20cancelled%20a%20planned%20visit%20to%20Saudi).%20While%20this%20position%20by%20the%20Trump%20administration%20delivered%20tremors%20across%20European%20capitals%2C%20it%20has%20also%20played%20into%20an%20increasingly%20constrained%20space%20between%20Riyadh%20and%20Abu%20Dhabi%20for%20regional%20influence.%20And%20peace%20diplomacy%2C%20or%20mediation%2C%20is%20the%20flavour%20of%20the%20day.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20the%20proverbial%20gold-rush%20to%20host%20Ukraine%20talks%20has%20more%20solid%20foundations%20in%20regional%20competition%20than%20an%20international%20one.%20For%20long%2C%20Oman%20has%20been%20the%20state%20that%20has%20consistently%20pitched%20itself%20as%20the%20main%20mediator%2C%20playing%20the%20role%20of%20%E2%80%98Switzerland%20of%20the%20Middle%20East'%2C%20where%20Muscat%20seemingly%20prioritises%20neutrality%20and%20offers%20a%20common%20ground%20for%20warring%20parties%2C%20such%20as%20Saudi%20Arabia%20and%20Yemen's%20Houthi%20militia%2C%20or%20even%20the%20US%20and%20Iran%2C%20to%20talk.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Qatar%20Question%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESaudi%20Arabia%20and%20the%20UAE%20installed%20a%20blockade%20against%20Qatar%20between%202017%20and%202021%20for%20what%20they%20saw%20as%20Doha%20not%20aligning%20and%20punching%20above%20its%20weight%2C%20and%2C%20more%20specifically%2C%20for%20its%20support%20for%20Political%20Islam.%20But%20the%20Qatari%20leadership%20had%20another%20trick%20up%20its%20sleeve%20to%20ratchet%20its%20power%20quotient.%20In%20February%202020%2C%20under%20Trump's%20first%20tenure%2C%20the%20Taliban%20in%20Afghanistan%20and%20the%20US%20signed%20a%20historic%20agreement%20for%20the%20latter's%20exit%20from%20a%20two-decade%20long%20war%20in%20the%20country.%20Doha%20hosted%20the%20political%20office%20for%20the%20Taliban%2C%20and%20managed%20Kabul%2C%20to%20deliver%20this%20outcome%20to%20a%20president%20who%2C%20more%20than%20anything%20else%2C%20adores%20deals.%20This%20%E2%80%9Csuccess%E2%80%9D%20gained%20Qatar%20the%20title%20of%20becoming%20America's%20first%20and%20preferred%20%E2%80%98major%20non-NATO%20ally'%20in%20the%20region.%20Today%2C%20Qatar%20also%20hosts%20America's%20largest%20military%20base%20in%20the%20Middle%20East.%20For%20others%2C%20such%20as%20the%20UAE%2C%20the%20meteoric%20rise%20of%20Qatar's%20influence%20in%20Washington%20was%20seen%20as%20a%20challenge.%20Within%20Abu%20Dhabi%2C%20questions%20were%20raised%20with%20Emirati%20diplomats%20in%20the%20US%20on%20why%20the%20Taliban's%20office%20was%20not%20hosted%20in%20either%20Abu%20Dhabi%20or%20Dubai.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ESaudi%20And%20UAE%20Have%20Bigger%20Goals%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20Saudi%20Arabia%2C%20despite%20its%20functional%20relations%20with%20Russia%20and%20China%20alike%2C%20a%20security%20relationship%20with%20the%20US%20remains%20paramount.%20The%20same%20strategic%20aim%20is%20consistent%20for%20the%20UAE%20as%20well%2C%20one%20of%20the%20few%20Arab%20states%20that%20normalised%20relations%20with%20Israel%20as%20part%20of%20the%20Trump-brokered%20Abraham%20Accords%20and%20which%20continues%20to%20have%20functional%20relations%20with%20Iran.%20Despite%20continuing%20pressures%20on%20Saudi%20Arabia%20and%20the%20UAE%20to%20help%20deliver%20lasting%20solutions%20to%20the%20Israel-Palestine%20crisis%20and%20the%20Israel-Hamas%20war%2C%20both%20have%20broader%2C%20long-term%20aims%20with%20regard%20to%20their%20positions%20as%20poles-of-power%20within%20a%20multipolar%20framework.%20Both%20Riyadh%20and%20Abu%20Dhabi%20share%20this%20world%20view%20with%20the%20likes%20of%20India%2C%20but%20American%20power%20projection%20is%20infinitely%20more%20critical%20to%20political%20structures%20in%20the%20Middle%20East.%20This%20is%20truer%20today%20after%20the%20experience%20of%20the%20Arab%20Spring%2C%20and%2C%20more%20recently%2C%20the%20collapse%20of%20the%20Bashar%20Al%20Assad%20regime%20in%20Syria%20at%20the%20hands%20of%20a%20self-styled%20%E2%80%98lapsed'%20jihadist%20group%2C%20the%20Hay'at%20Tahrir%20Al%20Sham%20(HTS).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EIs%20This%20The%20Future%20Of%20Mediation%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Saudis%20are%20not%20stopping%20just%20at%20giving%20space%20to%20the%20US%20and%20Russia%20to%20debate%20Ukraine.%20As%20per%20reports%2C%20Riyadh%20is%20also%20open%20to%20hosting%20talks%20between%20Iran%20and%20the%20US%20over%20the%20former's%20nuclear%20programme.%20The%20Saudi-Iran%20d%C3%A9tente%20was%20achieved%20in%20March%202023%20with%20the%20help%20of%20China%2C%20the%20main%20competitor%20to%20the%20US%2C%20and%20a%20state%20that%20has%20unreservedly%20supported%20Arab%20positions%20in%20Gaza.%20Beijing%2C%20meanwhile%2C%20also%20remains%20open%20to%20mediating%20and%20helping%20to%20bridge%20political%20gaps%20across%20the%20region.%20Chinese%20President%20Xi%20Jinping's%20visits%20to%20the%20region%20have%20been%20welcomed%20with%20gusto%20by%20Saudi%20Arabia%20and%20the%20UAE%20alike%2C%20both%20as%20a%20function%20of%20being%20the%20world's%20second-largest%20economic%20power%20and%20using%20this%20position%20to%20hedge%20risk%20with%20Western%20partners.%20The%20future%20of%20mediation%20between%20the%20Riyadh-Abu%20Dhabi-Doha%20trifecta%20is%20a%20cat%20and%20mouse%20game%20within%20the%20Arab%20construct.%20External%20powers%20such%20as%20the%20US%2C%20Russia%2C%20and%20China%2C%20are%20part%20of%20the%20utility%20kit.%20This%20push%20for%20one-upmanship%20will%20have%20a%20tremendous%20impact%20on%20regional%20politics%20where%20in%20the%20coming%20years%20economic%20and%20political%20competition%20is%20only%20expected%20to%20increase.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E(Kabir%20Taneja%20is%20Deputy%20Director%20and%20Fellow%2C%20Strategic%20Studies%20Programme%2C%20Observer%20Research%20Foundation)%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDisclaimer%3A%20These%20are%20the%20personal%20opinions%20of%20the%20author%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1739947860000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2025-02%2Fco13p5gs_russia-us-talks-in-saudi-arabia-over-ukraine-deal-afp_625x300_18_February_25.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Fus-russia-china-have-found-a-new-negotiating-table-in-middle-east-7744295%22%2C%22