p%20chimed%20in.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMusk%20seconded%20the%20President's%20claim%20and%20said%2C%20%26quot%3B%20Yes%2C%20they%20were%20left%20up%20there%20for%20political%20reasons%2C%20which%20is%20not%20good.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20asked%20about%20Space%20X's%20mission%20to%20bring%20back%20Sunita%20Williams%20and%20Butch%20Wilmore%2C%20Musk%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BWell%2C%20we%20don't%20want%20to%20be%20complacent%2C%20but%20we%20have%20brought%20astronauts%20back%20from%20the%20space%20station%20many%20times%20before%2C%20and%20always%20with%20success.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20asked%20about%20the%20timeline%20of%20the%20mission%2C%20Musk%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BI%20think%20it's%20about%20-%20about%20four%20weeks%20to%20bring%20them%20back.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20now%20have%20the%20go-ahead%2C%26quot%3B%20Trump%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYes.%20Well%2C%20thanks%20to%20you%2C%26quot%3B%20replied%20Musk.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETrump%20then%20claimed%20that%20Musk's%20company%20didn't%20have%20the%20go-ahead%20with%20the%20Biden%20administration.%20%26quot%3BHe%20(Biden)%20was%20going%20to%20leave%20him%20in%20space.%20%C2%A0I%20think%20he%20was%20going%20to%20leave%20them%20in%20space%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20Republican%20added.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Mission%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EButch%20Wilmore%20and%20Sunita%20Williams%20launched%20to%20the%20ISS%20aboard%20Boeing's%20Starliner%20spacecraft%20in%20June%202024.%20The%20flight%2C%20which%20was%20intended%20to%20last%20only%2010%20days%2C%20experienced%20a%20rocky%20journey.%20After%20arriving%20at%20the%20space%20station%2C%20NASA%20and%20Boeing%20worked%20for%20weeks%20to%20better%20understand%20the%20problems%20in%20the%20spacecraft%20but%20it%20was%20ultimately%20decided%20that%20it%20was%20too%20risky%20to%20return%20the%20Startliner%20with%20the%20crew.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFollowing%20this%2C%20in%20August%202024%